A two-year-old Malmesbury girl was reportedly beaten &amp; burnt with a cigarette last weekend. CAPE TOWN - A two-year-old Malmesbury girl remains in a stable condition in hospital after she was attacked, allegedly by her mother s boyfriend.It s alleged he beat the child and burnt her with a cigarette last weekend.It's believed the toddler was also sexually assaulted.The 24-year-old man is currently behind bars.Social Development MEC Albert Fritz says: We re saddened and horrified at the latest case. This department will have its own full investigation far from the police because this is absolutely abhorrent. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)